en_5703051_0	COLOMBO (News 1 st ) – Eight new State Ministers and ten New Deputy Ministers were sworn in today (May 02) in the presence of President Maithripala Sirisena.
en_5703051_1	The swearing in took place at the Presidential Secretariat at 10:30 AM.
en_5703051_2	Palitha Range Bandara took oaths as the new State Minister of Irrigation and Water Resources Management and Disaster Management.
en_5703051_3	Disaster Management is a new subject added to his State Ministerial portfolio.
en_5703051_4	Dilip Wedaarachchi took oaths as the State Minister of Fisheries and Aquatic Resources Development and Rural Economy.
en_5703051_5	Rural Economy is a new subject added to his State Ministerial portfolio.
en_5703051_6	M.L.A.M. Hizbullah was sworn in as the State Minister of Highways and Road Development, he previously held the subjects of Rehabilitation and Resettlement.
en_5703051_7	Mohan Lal Grero took oaths as the State Minister of Higher Education and Cultural Affairs – the latter is a new subject assigned to him.
en_5703051_8	Champika Premadasa who previously served as the State Minister for Industry and Commerce sworn in as the State Minister of Plantation Industries today.
en_5703051_9	Lakshman Seneviratne took oaths as the State Minister of Science, Technology and Research, Skills Development and Vocational Training, and Hill Country Heritage.
en_5703051_10	Sriyani Wijewickrama is the new State Minister of Sports, Provincial Councils and Local Government.
en_5703051_11	Weerakumara Dissanayake took oaths as the State Minister of Mahaweli Development, which was previously held by Mahinda Amaraweera.
en_5703051_12	Ameer Ali Shihabdeen was sworn in as the new Deputy Minister of Fisheries and Aquatic Resources Development and Rural Economy.
en_5703051_13	Dunesh Gankanda who was the Deputy Minister of Disaster Management was sworn in today as the new Deputy Minister of Lands and Parliamentary Reforms.
en_5703051_14	Ranjan Ramanayake took oaths as the Deputy Minister of Social Empowerment.
en_5703051_15	H. M. M. Harees who previously held the title Deputy Minister of Sports took oaths as the Deputy Minister of Public Enterprise and Kandy Development.
en_5703051_16	Karunarathna Paranawithana was sworn in as the Deputy Minister of Science, Technology and Research, Skills Development and Vocational Training, and Hill Country Heritage.
en_5703051_17	Sarathie Dushmantha took oaths as the Deputy Minister of Justice and Prison Reforms.
en_5703051_18	Palitha Kumara Thewarapperuma was sworn in as the Deputy Minister of Sustainable Development, Wildlife and Regional Development.
en_5703051_19	Muthu Sivalingam is the new Deputy Minister of Internal Affairs and Wayamba Development.
en_5703051_20	Manusha Nanayakkara took oaths as the Deputy Minister of Telecommunication, Digital Infrastructure and Foreign Employment.
